FBIS4-67232 "jptdd021__l94085" JPRS-TDD-94-021-L JPRS Narcotics 13 May 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA KAZAKHSTAN Further on Almaty Anticrime Effort Further on Almaty Anticrime Effort LD1305183494 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 1100 GMT 13 May 94 LD1305183494 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text]Armed military detachments have been introduced in Alma-Ata [Almaty] in a move to combat the rising wave of crime in the city. In four days of what our correspondent describes as essentially a state of emergency, more than 200 kg of hashish, marijuana and opium, and hundreds of weapons have been seized, 85 persons under investigation have been detained, 336 crimes have been solved soon after being committed, and 11 criminal groups have been made harmless. [Video shows armed detachments in streets; uniformed men on parade; guns, knives, ammunition laid out on a table]
